Uses of Package
com.iopipe.plugin

  • Packages that use com.iopipe.plugin 
    Package Description
    com.iopipe
    This package contians the classes and interfaces which are used to interact with the IOpipe service.
    com.iopipe.plugin
    This package contains the support for plugins which may be used to add functionality so that the client may utilize more monitoring tools.
    com.iopipe.plugin.profiler
    This package contains the profiler plugin which is used to profile code executions made by user code.
    com.iopipe.plugin.trace
    This contains the trace plugin implementation.
  • Classes in com.iopipe.plugin used by com.iopipe 
    Class and Description
    IOpipePluginExecution
    For plugins which provide access to information based on execution, this interface is used as a base for those plugins to provide functionality that is only needed per instance of a plugin.
    NoSuchPluginException
    This is thrown when a plugin was requested, but it does not exist or is disabled.
  • Classes in com.iopipe.plugin used by com.iopipe.plugin 
    Class and Description
    IOpipePlugin
    This interface represents the base of a plugin and is used to manage and create executable instances of plugins as they are needed.
    IOpipePluginExecution
    For plugins which provide access to information based on execution, this interface is used as a base for those plugins to provide functionality that is only needed per instance of a plugin.
  • Classes in com.iopipe.plugin used by com.iopipe.plugin.profiler 
    Class and Description
    IOpipePlugin
    This interface represents the base of a plugin and is used to manage and create executable instances of plugins as they are needed.
    IOpipePluginExecution
    For plugins which provide access to information based on execution, this interface is used as a base for those plugins to provide functionality that is only needed per instance of a plugin.
    IOpipePluginPostExecutable
    This interface is used for plugins which require that when the method being traced has finished executing, that it should perform some final operations as needed.
    IOpipePluginPreExecutable
    This interface is used for plugins which must be initialized and setup before the logged method begins execution.
